new-page: true

= What was

[? if ending = "aniquilacion" : The Mexican Communist Party ceased to exist as a national organization at some point not even its enemies could date. There was no final communique; organizations do not die of one shot but of a thousand casualties without funerals. Its archives — the ones the DFS never captured — slept in three basements in three cities, waiting for historians who would take decades to arrive. ?]

[? if ending = "debil" : The Movement survived — which in this country and this era is a transitive verb: it survived THE dirty war, THE charrismo, THE charola. It ended small, battered, with more martyrs than militants — but with the list intact, the paper printing, and in three or four corners of the Republic, people who never sold. ?]

[? if ending = "media" : The Movement came out of the long decade as something that seemed impossible in 1968: a real national organization — present in the factories, in the Montana of Guerrero, in the normal schools and universities, with tested cadres and a press the regime read with professional attention. It was not power. It was, for the first time in a generation, the possibility of power. ?]

[? if ending = "fuerte" : What came out of the decade nobody had budgeted for, Bucareli least of all: a mass left — still a minority, but a mass — with real presence among workers despite don Fidel, a peasant base in three states, the generation of 68 formed in its ranks, and a national sympathy the regime could no longer round to zero. The political reform was not a gracious concession. It was a recognition of force. Yours. ?]

[? if ending = "reconocimiento" : The impossible, with a date on it: on the sixth of July, 1988, the Republic voted, the system attempted its greatest alquimia, and the alquimia broke against twenty years of watched casillas, duplicated actas, and witnesses who did not go home to sleep. An elected president took office. The apparatus did not die — apparatuses never do — but from that night on it governs a country that knows how to count. ?]

[? if ending = "historico" : The fraud was consummated; the country that watched it did not come apart. Out of the wave and the wound came, in May of 1989, the new party — founded on the registro your Movement carried for two decades, with the cadres you formed and the lists you kept. It was not the victory. It was the founding of the house where victory, someday, would have an address to arrive at. ?]

[? if ending = "ruptura" : Eleven days the Republic will neither forget nor forgive nor resolve: the country stopped, the state answering in its oldest language, and the lists growing at a pace memory could barely sustain. History will judge the match — you struck it, with open eyes — and no version of that judgment will be able to say the people were unwilling. ?]

[? if ending = "irrelevancia" : The wave passed you by. Coherence was preserved whole — program, independence, tradition — and history, which rewards presence rather than coherence, founded its next decade under other names. What remains: the cadres, the analysis, and the question with no statute of limitations: what is the use of being right in the next room? ?]

[? if memorial >= 6 : The list carries [+ memorial +] names added in these years. It was kept complete: name, date, place. None of the three copies fell. ?]
[? if memorial >= 1 and memorial <= 5 : The list carries [+ memorial +] names added in these years. Few, for the decade it was. Enough to never sleep quite the same. ?]

- @slide_faltas: Continue.

@slide_faltas
new-page: true

= What was not

[? if postura_guerrilla = 1 : The deslinde from the armed road kept the Party alive and legal-in-waiting — and left the bravest generation of the era to die alone in the sierras and the safe houses. If there was another road, nobody found it in time. The corridos do not forgive, and neither do the minutes. ?]
[? if postura_guerrilla = 2 : The calculated ambiguity proved exactly that: calculated, by both sides. The DFS never forgave you; the guerrilla never embraced you. The wire was walked — but a wire is not a bridge. ?]
[? if postura_guerrilla = 3 : The discreet channels saved lives no archive will ever count, and cost a mortgage of expediente paid with interest. When the history is written, that line will not appear — which was the point. ?]
[? if postura_guerrilla = 0 : On the armed question the Movement never said anything, which was its way of saying everything. Silence was the only line executed to perfection. ?]

[? if charrismo >= 80 : The charro wall ended the era intact. Don Fidel buried another challenge and kept smoking; the working class remained organized by the state against itself. The Mexican century largest unpaid debt remains unpaid. ?]
[? if charrismo < 80 : The charro wall ended the era cracked — not broken, but cracked in plain sight, and walls that crack once are surveyed differently forever. ?]

[? if registro = 0 : And the electoral door was never opened: without registro, a million hands writing names the Comision burns unread. What the reform made possible, others will play. Or you — in the next of history rounds. ?]

