= Snapshot: a book, 2014

*(From "El siglo de las izquierdas en Mexico", Fondo de Cultura Economica, 2014 — chapter 7, translated:)*

[? if ending = "aniquilacion" : "...by the late seventies the old party was already the property of doctoral theses rather than police reports. The question that organizes this chapter is not why it disappeared — causes abound — but why its disappearance mattered so much: for half a century it had been the only institutional deposit of a memory the state required not to exist. When the deposit closed, memory passed to private hands: mothers, widows, schoolteachers with notebooks. It would take twenty years to find premises again." ?]

[? if ending = "debil" or ending = "media" : "...historiography has been unjust to that short decade. Seen from 1988 it looks like a mere prologue; seen from inside, it was politics in its phase of primitive accumulation: every assembly in Nezahualcoyotl, every contested teachers section, every list of the disappeared preserved against all practical reason, constituted the capital with which the left arrived — thin but alive — at the door that 1977 half-opened. The protagonists of this book did not know they were a prologue. They worked as if they were the whole volume." ?]

[? if ending = "fuerte" : "...it should be remembered that none of it was written in advance. In October of 1968 the Mexican left was five thousand militants with sealed offices and imprisoned cadres. That a decade later it was the force that obliged the state to reform constitutes one of the rare Latin American cases in which an organization defeated in the plaza remade the board without taking a single palace." ?]

[? if ending = "reconocimiento" : "...the manuals call the Mexican 88 the first counted transition: not a pact of elites but a ledger defended. The lampara — as the cadres called their casilla network — proved the century most improbable revolutionary instrument: a form, guarded by rural schoolteachers, against which a sixty-year regime broke." ?]

[? if ending = "historico" : "...the founding paradox of 88: the fraud triumphed and, in triumphing, manufactured its own gravedigger. The party born in May of 1989 inherited from the old movement its infrastructure, its martyrology and its arithmetical stubbornness; from cardenismo, the millions. Mexican democratization, one of its architects would later write, was the illegitimate daughter of that night of dead screens." ?]

[? if ending = "ruptura" : "...over the Eleven Days the historiography maintains a civil war of its own: crushed insurrection, or a general strike betrayed by its own grandeur? What is not disputed: after 1988 the Mexican state never again pretended normality, and the lists — all three copies survived — founded the jurisprudence of memory that would, decades later, seat the responsible before judges." ?]

[? if ending = "irrelevancia" : "...a chapter apart belongs to the historic left that arrived whole and alone at the shore of 88: its program was the most coherent of the era, and its absence from the wave remains the most studied decision in Mexican political science, which has used it ever since as the classic illustration that, in transitions, presence is the only theory that votes." ?]

