= Snapshot: a thread, 2019

**ForoMexico / History / What actually happened to the 70s left?**

**tlacuache_rojo:** My grandmother says she hid the party mimeograph on her roof in 71. Anyone else have stories like this or is my abuela pulling my leg?

[? if ending = "aniquilacion" : **doctor_atl_fan:** She is not. There was a whole network. It got eaten alive between the DFS and the internal wars. My uncle says the saddest part was not the repression — it was that by the end there was no one left to tell. ?]

[? if ending = "aniquilacion" : **moderador_charro:** Thread locked for politics. You know the rules. ?]

[? if ending = "debil" or ending = "media" : **doctor_atl_fan:** My dad sold the paper outside the SEP. He says they were four cats, but the four cats kept THE LIST. That list is in the memory museum now, if you feel like crying a little. ?]

[? if ending = "debil" or ending = "media" : **ana.sin.acentos:** The wild part is that half of today social movements come out of that. Scratch any democratic union or neighborhood committee and there is one of those old-timers underneath. ?]

[? if ending = "fuerte" : **doctor_atl_fan:** "What happened"? Compa, half of today political map descends from it. The detail they skip in school — when the government "opened up" in 77, it was not kindness. It opened because it could no longer count to a hundred without a million annulled votes left over. ?]

[? if ending = "fuerte" : **tlacuache_rojo:** LOL the Campa corrido my abuela sings says exactly that — "un millon de nombres que el gobierno no conto." ?]

[? if ending = "reconocimiento" : **doctor_atl_fan:** My mom was a casilla representative in 88. She still has her copy of the acta, framed. She says when "the system crashed," nobody at her casilla moved: "let it crash — WE already counted." ?]

[? if ending = "historico" : **doctor_atl_fan:** What nobody tells you: today big party exists because the old-timers NEVER let go of the registro. Decades hauling papers from basement to basement so there would be somewhere to found something the night it was needed. Heroic bureaucracy — that is the technical term. ?]

[? if ending = "ruptura" : **doctor_atl_fan:** My uncle was in the Eleven Days. He will not talk about it. He talks about the day BEFORE — says he has never again seen the country that awake, and that is why he regrets nothing. Screenshot this thread, they are going to lock it. ?]

[? if ending = "irrelevancia" : **doctor_atl_fan:** That is my grandparents party. Serious program, serious people — and in 88 they watched the wave from the shore, out of purity. My grandfather calls it "coherence." My grandmother, who was in the CEU, uses a different word. ?]

