= Snapshot: a transcript, 2023

*(Auto-generated transcript, video: "I interviewed my great-grandmother about 68" — 340K views)*

—Were you afraid, bisabuela?

—Every day, mijo. Fear was not the rare thing. The rare thing was the people who did the work with the fear still on.

[? if ending = "aniquilacion" : —Was it worth it, if it all ended? ?]

[? if ending = "aniquilacion" : —(long pause in the video) ...The apparatus ended, mijo. Apparatuses end. What we made with our hands is still out there, it just does not carry a card anymore. You, for example. You are here asking me. We made that too. ?]

[? if ending = "debil" or ending = "media" : —And did it help anything? ?]

[? if ending = "debil" or ending = "media" : —Look: every name we wrote down, somebody came searching for later. Every name. When the archives opened, the families arrived carrying OUR lists, because the government lists lied. It helped. It took forty years, but it helped. Patience is also a form of politics — just the kind that never gets photographed. ?]

[? if ending = "fuerte" : —At school they told us your generation changed the country. ?]

[? if ending = "fuerte" : —(laughs) It took us twenty years to win the first election they counted for us. TWENTY YEARS, mijo. People think history is the day of the triumph. No. History is the nineteen years, eleven months and twenty-nine days before it, with the rain coming down and the mimeograph broken. Write that down for your video. ?]

[? if ending = "reconocimiento" : —What did you do that night, bisabuela? ?]

[? if ending = "reconocimiento" : —I counted, mijo. All of Mexico counted that night. That is why I laugh when they say democracy was given to us: I watched it being added up, column by column, in pencil. ?]

[? if ending = "historico" : —Were you not furious they stole the election? ?]

[? if ending = "historico" : —The fury has lasted me to this day. But look: from the theft we built a house. On the sixth of July we lost a president and gained a people that never again went along quietly. In the long run, I could not tell you which was worth more. ?]

[? if ending = "ruptura" : —Were you in the Eleven Days, bisabuela? ?]

[? if ending = "ruptura" : —(silence) ...Just write down this much: do not let anyone tell you it was madness. It was the most expensive sanity of my life. And write down the names — that is what we always kept the list for. ?]

[? if ending = "irrelevancia" : —Why did your people not join the wave in 88? ?]

[? if ending = "irrelevancia" : —We had reasons, mijo. Very good ones. So good I still recite them alone in the kitchen, to see if they can convince the walls. ?]

- @slide_mural: Continue.

@slide_mural
new-page: true
face-image: img/rivera_mural.jpg

= El muro, de nuevo

Go back to the stairwell. Look up at Rivera's wall one more time — Zapata, the white horse, the word *Tierra* — and ask the only question the mural was ever really asking: did any of it come down off the plaster?

[? if ending = "reconocimiento" or ending = "historico" or ending = "fuerte" : Once — on one counted night, in one founded party, in one arithmetic the state could not rewrite — the dream stepped down off the wall and stood in the plaza on its own feet. It did not stay long, and it did not do everything the painter promised. But a thing that was only ever paint had, for a season, a pulse. The mural is still up there. It is no longer the only place the dream lives. ?]

[? if ending = "debil" or ending = "media" or ending = "ruptura" or ending = "irrelevancia" : The dream did not come down off the wall — not this decade, not on your watch. But look closely at the plaster: it is worn where a thousand hands reached up and touched it, year after year, refusing to accept that a painted promise is only paint. The mural outlasts the men who commissioned it precisely because people like you would not let it dry into decoration. The appointment is still unkept. Someone is still, always, at the door of the agrarian office. The dream continues because it was never allowed to finish being a dream. ?]

[? if ending = "aniquilacion" or ending = "intervencion" : The dream was larger than the room they gave it, and the room won — this time. They hosed the plaza clean; they will not scrub the wall, because a mural of a revolution safely dead is the regime's favorite kind. And yet: paint outlives painters. The campesino is still bent to the corn up there, the worker still holds the future in his two hands, and somewhere a mother is telling a boy what the figures mean. It always begins again. It always begins again. But not, this time, with you. ?]

The mother in Michoacán grew old. The campesino on the Costa Grande died at the door of the office, still holding the paper. The railwayman, at the end, got his name into a court document instead of a ledger. None of them saw the dawn on the wall. All of them were the reason the paint never quite dried.

- @terminar: Fin.

